#DESCRIPTION
#Representation of function as a power series
#ENDDESCRIPTION

#KEYWORDS('Power Series'  )

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(1,5);
$a2 = 2*$a;
$c0 = $a;
$c1 = 0;
$c2 = -1/(2*$a);
$c3 = 0;
$c4 = -1/(8*$a**3);

BEGIN_TEXT

The Taylor 
series for \( f(x) = \sqrt{$a2 x - x^2}  \) at \( a = $a \)  is \(
\sum_{n=0}^\infty
c_n( x - $a )^n. \) $BR
Find the first few coefficients. $BR
\( c_0 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_1 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_2 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_3 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_4 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR
The left endpoint of the interval of convergence for the series is
\{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR
The right endpoint of the interval of convergence for the series is
\{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR
END_TEXT


&ANS(std_num_cmp($c0) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp($c1) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp($c2) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp($c3) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp($c4) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp(0) );
&ANS(std_num_cmp($a2) );
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the
#problem.
